1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:01:03,393 --> 00:01:05,383
What are you doing?

3
00:01:05,383 --> 00:01:07,718
What do you think you're doing right now?

4
00:01:07,718 --> 00:01:08,886
Well...

5
00:01:08,886 --> 00:01:11,097
I was just...

6
00:01:13,408 --> 00:01:15,491
Is that why you came back into our lives?

7
00:01:15,491 --> 00:01:16,521
For the money?

8
00:01:16,521 --> 00:01:18,007
I just needed to cover something urgent.

9
00:01:18,007 --> 00:01:19,493
I was going to put it back.

10
00:01:19,493 --> 00:01:21,122
- I swear.
- How could you do this?

11
00:01:21,122 --> 00:01:22,290
We're family.

12
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:23,916
Yeah, exactly.

13
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:28,129
When family's struggling,
can't we help each other out?

14
00:01:29,369 --> 00:01:32,255
Then the call to the insurance company...

15
00:01:32,841 --> 00:01:34,815
Was that you too?

16
00:01:34,815 --> 00:01:37,062
It was. So what?

17
00:01:37,062 --> 00:01:39,348
Did I commit some kind of crime?

18
00:01:39,348 --> 00:01:40,921
Technically speaking,

19
00:01:40,921 --> 00:01:43,379
I have a right to part of that insurance money.

20
00:01:43,379 --> 00:01:44,759
I raised Woo Jin all these years.

21
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:46,547
That has to count for something.

22
00:01:46,547 --> 00:01:48,524
And what about Woo Joo?

23
00:01:48,524 --> 00:01:49,775
Woo Joo...

24
00:01:49,775 --> 00:01:51,733
He is Woo Jin's child.

25
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:54,868
Your own grandson!

26
00:01:55,617 --> 00:01:56,935
Fine.

27
00:01:56,935 --> 00:01:59,674
Then let's include Woo Joo too.

28
00:01:59,674 --> 00:02:01,311
Split it four ways.

29
00:02:01,311 --> 00:02:03,671
Fair and square.

30
00:02:05,847 --> 00:02:07,954
Get out.

31
00:02:09,126 --> 00:02:11,407
Get out of here. Right now!

32
00:02:11,407 --> 00:02:12,825
Hey, let go.

33
00:02:12,825 --> 00:02:14,903
Do you know how hard I worked for this?

34
00:02:14,903 --> 00:02:16,819
Let go.

35
00:02:21,137 --> 00:02:22,836
Darn it!

36
00:02:36,432 --> 00:02:37,700
Hyun Jin,

37
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,731
are you okay?

38
00:02:42,897 --> 00:02:44,249
Are you out insane?

39
00:02:44,249 --> 00:02:46,639
[Myeongin Police Station]

40
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,431
[Episode 9]

41
00:02:47,431 --> 00:02:49,070
He has multiple prior convictions
for the same offense,

42
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:51,897
and he's currently on parole,
so he'll be taken into custody immediately.

43
00:02:51,897 --> 00:02:54,617
Mr. Sun Gyu Tae was serving time
for fraud until recently.

44
00:02:54,617 --> 00:02:57,036
You really didn't know?

45
00:02:58,393 --> 00:03:00,236
Yes.

46
00:03:00,905 --> 00:03:02,198
We're told

47
00:03:02,198 --> 00:03:03,918
you deliberately approached them

48
00:03:03,918 --> 00:03:06,844
for the insurance money and other valuables.

49
00:03:06,844 --> 00:03:08,634
Mr. Sun Gyu Tae,

50
00:03:08,634 --> 00:03:09,889
is that true?

51
00:03:09,889 --> 00:03:11,610
Come on.

52
00:03:11,610 --> 00:03:13,218
Let's be real.

53
00:03:13,218 --> 00:03:17,374
Do you know how much it costs to raise kids?

54
00:03:17,374 --> 00:03:19,266
What I've spent raising them all these years,

55
00:03:19,266 --> 00:03:21,340
don't I deserve to get that back?

56
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:23,858
Please, stop!

57
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:28,485
Please...

58
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:32,499
Just stop.

59
00:03:38,205 --> 00:03:40,378
Mr. Sun Tae Hyung.

60
00:03:44,628 --> 00:03:47,416
You're Woo Jin's brother, right?

61
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:48,906
Who are you?

62
00:03:48,906 --> 00:03:52,220
I'm Inspector Jeon Min Cheol
from Myeongin Police Station.

63
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:55,074
Could we speak for a moment?

64
00:04:09,081 --> 00:04:12,067
You'll need to disinfect the wound
every two to three days,

65
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:15,265
and keep it dry for now.

66
00:04:15,265 --> 00:04:17,398
If it starts to swell,

67
00:04:17,398 --> 00:04:18,798
come back in right away.

68
00:04:18,798 --> 00:04:20,722
- I will.
- All set.

69
00:04:20,722 --> 00:04:22,476
Start her on an IV.

70
00:04:22,476 --> 00:04:24,723
Thank you.

71
00:04:28,392 --> 00:04:29,542
Hello.

72
00:04:29,542 --> 00:04:31,714
Hello.

73
00:04:33,122 --> 00:04:34,795
Sir,

74
00:04:34,795 --> 00:04:38,207
Tae Hyung said something urgent came up.

75
00:04:38,207 --> 00:04:40,847
What should we do about the meeting?

76
00:04:40,847 --> 00:04:42,229
Mr. Tae Hyung too?

77
00:04:42,229 --> 00:04:44,608
Ms. Hyun Jin also took a sudden day off today.

78
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:47,021
Did something happen between them?

79
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:50,614
Things were chaotic at the funeral.

80
00:04:50,614 --> 00:04:53,842
I didn't get a chance
to properly introduce myself.

81
00:04:53,842 --> 00:04:55,362
Well...

82
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:58,068
I worked with Woo Jin.

83
00:04:59,378 --> 00:05:01,755
I was his senior.

84
00:05:01,755 --> 00:05:04,491
So what was it you needed to tell me?

85
00:05:04,491 --> 00:05:06,349
I wasn't sure

86
00:05:06,349 --> 00:05:09,311
if I should say anything

87
00:05:09,311 --> 00:05:12,878
or just pretend I didn't know.

88
00:05:12,878 --> 00:05:14,321
Actually...

89
00:05:14,321 --> 00:05:18,490
Woo Jin didn't want you
to ever find out about this.

90
00:05:18,490 --> 00:05:20,914
That's why I hesitated.

91
00:05:20,914 --> 00:05:23,474
What are you saying?

92
00:05:25,398 --> 00:05:27,520
Sun Gyu Tae.

93
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:31,376
You've heard he served time for fraud, right?

94
00:05:31,376 --> 00:05:32,427
Yes.

95
00:05:32,427 --> 00:05:35,410
Woo Jin was the one

96
00:05:35,410 --> 00:05:38,003
who put him behind bars.

97
00:05:40,163 --> 00:05:43,849
That's why he became a police officer.

98
00:05:44,910 --> 00:05:47,442
About seven years ago,

99
00:05:47,442 --> 00:05:49,122
a fraud case came in

100
00:05:49,122 --> 00:05:52,419
to our substation.

101
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:54,486
[Complaint]
[Complainant: Park Sung Ho]

102
00:05:54,486 --> 00:05:57,459
[Defendant: Sun Gyu Tae]

103
00:06:04,707 --> 00:06:05,817
Just a moment.

104
00:06:05,817 --> 00:06:07,301
Yes.

105
00:06:07,301 --> 00:06:08,327
What's this?

106
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:10,356
You still haven't handed this over?

107
00:06:10,356 --> 00:06:12,210
We've got a mountain of cases.

108
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:14,156
Why are you dragging this one out?

109
00:06:14,156 --> 00:06:16,005
Just file the report

110
00:06:16,005 --> 00:06:17,547
and send it up the chain.

111
00:06:17,547 --> 00:06:20,255
If we send it up like this,
he'll get a year at most.

112
00:06:20,255 --> 00:06:22,662
There have to be more victims if we dig deeper.

113
00:06:22,662 --> 00:06:25,108
It's not even our case.
What are you trying to do?

114
00:06:25,108 --> 00:06:26,165
Please.

115
00:06:26,165 --> 00:06:28,208
What's wrong with you?

116
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:31,684
You know the victim or something?

117
00:06:32,370 --> 00:06:35,016
Not the victim. The suspect.

118
00:06:35,016 --> 00:06:36,969
What?

119
00:06:38,017 --> 00:06:39,930
He's my father.

120
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:42,497
Woo Jin tracked down

121
00:06:42,497 --> 00:06:45,287
every victim Sun Gyu Tae scammed.

122
00:06:45,287 --> 00:06:48,332
So I asked him

123
00:06:48,332 --> 00:06:50,117
what kind of history he had with his father

124
00:06:50,117 --> 00:06:54,077
that made him so determined to lock him up.

125
00:07:01,403 --> 00:07:04,077
It's nothing special.

126
00:07:04,077 --> 00:07:06,823
A man who seemed fine

127
00:07:06,823 --> 00:07:09,220
loses his business overnight,

128
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,920
starts obsessing over money,

129
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:14,391
drinks more and more.

130
00:07:14,391 --> 00:07:17,240
Then on the days he drank...

131
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:19,396
He got violent.

132
00:07:19,396 --> 00:07:21,717
What?

133
00:07:21,717 --> 00:07:24,361
You mean... Sun Gyu Tae

134
00:07:24,361 --> 00:07:27,207
hit you too?

135
00:07:27,207 --> 00:07:30,035
The first time's the hardest.

136
00:07:30,035 --> 00:07:33,170
After that, you just get used to it.

137
00:07:34,841 --> 00:07:37,324
But when I saw him

138
00:07:37,324 --> 00:07:41,144
raise his hand at Tae Hyung,

139
00:07:41,144 --> 00:07:44,471
that's when it hit me.

140
00:07:45,991 --> 00:07:48,553
I was like, I couldn't let it go on.

141
00:07:48,553 --> 00:07:50,704
I had to report him.

142
00:07:50,704 --> 00:07:54,017
He didn't have any other record. Right?

143
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:58,743
Well, I had a plan.

144
00:07:58,743 --> 00:08:00,516
I'd leave Tae Hyung somewhere safe,

145
00:08:00,516 --> 00:08:02,530
at a children's home,

146
00:08:02,530 --> 00:08:05,200
then report him.

147
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:08,766
I thought that would be enough.

148
00:08:09,758 --> 00:08:12,458
But it failed. Every time.

149
00:08:13,616 --> 00:08:16,083
As you know, back then,

150
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:18,038
they'd call it "discipline."

151
00:08:18,038 --> 00:08:21,378
Say it was a father's right.

152
00:08:23,318 --> 00:08:26,564
I reported him over and over.

153
00:08:26,564 --> 00:08:29,192
Kept running away.

154
00:08:29,192 --> 00:08:32,085
Got dragged back and beaten.

155
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,092
It just kept repeating...

156
00:08:37,092 --> 00:08:39,744
And before I knew it, years had gone by.

157
00:08:39,744 --> 00:08:41,481
But...

158
00:08:41,481 --> 00:08:42,943
You were just a kid too.

159
00:08:42,943 --> 00:08:45,130
You needed someone to lean on.

160
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:47,401
The only way

161
00:08:48,154 --> 00:08:52,585
I could protect Tae Hyung from our father

162
00:08:52,585 --> 00:08:55,028
was to keep him

163
00:08:55,028 --> 00:08:57,730
out of that house.

164
00:09:01,870 --> 00:09:05,974
I thought once we were adults,
it would all be over.

165
00:09:07,123 --> 00:09:08,449
But he'd show up again,

166
00:09:08,449 --> 00:09:11,152
asking for money,

167
00:09:11,152 --> 00:09:13,495
and that's when I realized...

168
00:09:15,317 --> 00:09:17,858
At least Tae Hyung

169
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:21,483
was free from him.

170
00:09:21,483 --> 00:09:24,023
That was enough for me.

171
00:09:24,023 --> 00:09:26,477
You idiot.

172
00:09:26,477 --> 00:09:28,249
Hey.

173
00:09:28,249 --> 00:09:31,152
Why would you live like that?

174
00:09:31,152 --> 00:09:33,161
Why?

175
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:38,238
Because I'm the older brother.

176
00:09:39,055 --> 00:09:41,029
That's...

177
00:09:41,029 --> 00:09:43,568
what an older brother does.

178
00:09:43,568 --> 00:09:46,161
Because I'm his brother.

179
00:09:54,342 --> 00:09:56,402
Here.

180
00:10:02,961 --> 00:10:05,213
[Complainant: Sun Woo Jin]
[Defendant: Sun Gyu Tae]

181
00:10:05,213 --> 00:10:07,379
[Complainant: Sun Woo Jin]
[My dad would hit me for small mistakes.]

182
00:10:07,379 --> 00:10:09,733
Sun Gyu Tae started hitting Woo Jin

183
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:11,260
when he was in eighth grade.

184
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:12,886
[Reason for Complaint: He repeatedly
abused me while intoxicated.]

185
00:10:12,886 --> 00:10:15,593
As you can see,

186
00:10:15,593 --> 00:10:18,639
the abuse went on for quite some time.

187
00:10:19,306 --> 00:10:21,319
By the time he put Sun Gyu Tae in prison,

188
00:10:21,319 --> 00:10:24,564
too much time had already passed.

189
00:10:24,564 --> 00:10:26,327
And after that,

190
00:10:26,327 --> 00:10:27,895
he couldn't bring himself

191
00:10:27,895 --> 00:10:30,958
to come find you.

192
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:33,481
No...

193
00:10:34,309 --> 00:10:35,702
That can't be.

194
00:10:35,702 --> 00:10:38,122
Why would he...

195
00:10:40,747 --> 00:10:44,837
He was worried about what would happen
after Sun Gyu Tae got out.

196
00:11:11,029 --> 00:11:12,073
[Temporary helper]

197
00:11:23,476 --> 00:11:26,389
Why isn't he answering?

198
00:12:29,156 --> 00:12:32,636
Woo Jin said he was able to endure it

199
00:12:32,636 --> 00:12:35,579
because of you.

200
00:12:42,322 --> 00:12:46,951
[Moonlight Children's Home]

201
00:12:51,769 --> 00:12:55,442
When he saw you doing well,

202
00:12:57,118 --> 00:13:00,450
he felt like he could handle anything.

203
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:02,802
Even to a fault.

204
00:13:46,644 --> 00:13:49,831
[Assistant Sun Tae Hyung]

205
00:14:00,107 --> 00:14:03,076
Who asked you to do that?

206
00:14:06,694 --> 00:14:11,081
Why did you carry all of it alone
instead of telling me?

207
00:14:15,148 --> 00:14:18,116
Did you think I'd be grateful?

208
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:23,846
If you were going to do this...

209
00:14:27,047 --> 00:14:31,140
you shouldn't have left like that.

210
00:14:31,818 --> 00:14:34,738
You can't just leave me like this.

211
00:14:37,982 --> 00:14:40,901
What am I supposed to do?

212
00:14:45,939 --> 00:14:49,025
What am I supposed to do?

213
00:15:12,611 --> 00:15:14,262
Oh, hey.

214
00:15:14,262 --> 00:15:16,556
You were home.

215
00:15:18,404 --> 00:15:21,158
Why weren't you answering your phone?

216
00:15:21,158 --> 00:15:24,351
Sorry. I had a lot on my mind.

217
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:31,663
You should put some ointment on that.

218
00:15:34,825 --> 00:15:37,622
What did the doctor say?

219
00:15:37,622 --> 00:15:40,895
He said it's nothing serious. I'm fine.

220
00:15:41,635 --> 00:15:44,227
What about you?

221
00:15:44,227 --> 00:15:46,435
Are you okay?

222
00:15:49,218 --> 00:15:51,393
You must've been shaken up. Get some rest.

223
00:15:51,393 --> 00:15:53,041
I'm heading out for a bit.

224
00:15:53,041 --> 00:15:56,467
- What?
- Don't wait up.

225
00:16:24,297 --> 00:16:26,543
[Kim Ui Jun]

226
00:16:33,994 --> 00:16:36,207
You know...

227
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:39,392
The day of the accident.

228
00:16:39,392 --> 00:16:41,806
That was the day

229
00:16:43,487 --> 00:16:47,120
Woo Jin got the text
about my father being released.

230
00:16:49,597 --> 00:16:51,123
Tae Hyung, it's me.

231
00:16:51,123 --> 00:16:53,077
I need to tell you something.

232
00:16:53,077 --> 00:16:54,509
Call me back.

233
00:16:54,509 --> 00:16:56,522
That's why he was trying to reach me.

234
00:16:56,522 --> 00:16:58,969
To tell me that.

235
00:17:00,843 --> 00:17:03,317
I didn't even know...

236
00:17:04,253 --> 00:17:07,213
You couldn't have known.

237
00:17:07,213 --> 00:17:09,746
That's the problem.

238
00:17:11,495 --> 00:17:14,938
Like an idiot, I didn't know anything...

239
00:17:14,938 --> 00:17:18,804
and people got hurt because of me.

240
00:17:24,173 --> 00:17:26,206
If...

241
00:17:28,518 --> 00:17:31,878
If I had answered the call that day...

242
00:17:33,994 --> 00:17:38,360
maybe my brother and his wife
would still be alive.

243
00:17:41,592 --> 00:17:45,473
I've never once been any help to him.

244
00:17:48,207 --> 00:17:51,263
It feels like this is all my fault.

245
00:17:55,256 --> 00:17:58,236
If it weren't for me,

246
00:17:59,134 --> 00:18:02,468
maybe he wouldn't have lived like that.

247
00:18:07,157 --> 00:18:09,190
And maybe...

248
00:18:12,410 --> 00:18:14,254
that accident wouldn't have happened.

249
00:18:14,254 --> 00:18:17,054
Hey, don't say that.

250
00:18:24,045 --> 00:18:27,035
I actually went

251
00:18:27,035 --> 00:18:29,217
to my brother's wedding.

252
00:18:29,217 --> 00:18:31,234
First, the groom

253
00:18:31,234 --> 00:18:34,300
will place the ring on the bride.

254
00:18:51,819 --> 00:18:54,477
Don't live too happily.

255
00:18:58,214 --> 00:19:01,394
I should've just told him to be happy.

256
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:09,919
If I'd known that was the last time...

257
00:19:12,415 --> 00:19:15,101
I wouldn't have said that.

258
00:19:22,763 --> 00:19:25,576
Hopping, hopping.

259
00:19:25,576 --> 00:19:27,658
Time for bed.

260
00:19:27,658 --> 00:19:28,726
No.

261
00:19:28,726 --> 00:19:30,915
- Can't sleep?
- Yeah.

262
00:19:30,915 --> 00:19:32,862
- It's raining.
- Raining?

263
00:19:32,862 --> 00:19:34,662
Yeah.

264
00:19:37,535 --> 00:19:39,730
Uncle...

265
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:41,873
What?

266
00:19:41,873 --> 00:19:44,976
- Do you miss Uncle?
- Yeah.

267
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:48,248
He's going to be late tonight.

268
00:19:48,248 --> 00:19:49,822
You should sleep first.

269
00:19:49,822 --> 00:19:51,441
No.

270
00:19:51,441 --> 00:19:53,955
I think Uncle's heart

271
00:19:53,955 --> 00:19:57,241
really, really hurts.

272
00:20:01,688 --> 00:20:04,174
It's raining pretty hard.

273
00:20:05,985 --> 00:20:07,527
Will he be okay?

274
00:20:07,527 --> 00:20:11,020
It's raining pretty hard.

275
00:20:17,435 --> 00:20:19,217
Yes.

276
00:20:19,217 --> 00:20:21,449
I saw the outfits you sent.

277
00:20:21,449 --> 00:20:24,322
They don't really match the shoot concept.

278
00:20:24,322 --> 00:20:26,115
Then, please.

279
00:20:26,115 --> 00:20:28,103
Thank you.

280
00:20:30,986 --> 00:20:33,083
Hey, Sun Tae Hyung.

281
00:20:34,302 --> 00:20:37,299
You look awful today.

282
00:20:37,299 --> 00:20:38,825
What's with all those wounds?

283
00:20:38,825 --> 00:20:41,011
Got into a fight or something?

284
00:20:41,011 --> 00:20:43,299
It's nothing.

285
00:20:43,889 --> 00:20:45,140
Sun Tae Hyung,

286
00:20:45,140 --> 00:20:46,541
for people like us,

287
00:20:46,541 --> 00:20:49,144
our face is everything.

288
00:20:49,144 --> 00:20:52,990
Keep putting ointment on it before it scars.

289
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:57,041
Thanks.

290
00:20:58,653 --> 00:21:01,953
Wait, aren't you off today?

291
00:21:03,418 --> 00:21:06,166
I just wanted to stay busy.

292
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:08,246
I sent over the retouched shots
from the last shoot.

293
00:21:08,246 --> 00:21:09,497
Could you take a look?

294
00:21:09,497 --> 00:21:11,041
Already?

295
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:12,209
Oh, right.

296
00:21:12,209 --> 00:21:14,836
The ARKO next season campaign.

297
00:21:14,836 --> 00:21:17,615
They want the concept draft
as soon as possible.

298
00:21:17,615 --> 00:21:19,282
I'm finishing it up.

299
00:21:19,282 --> 00:21:21,115
That fast?

300
00:21:21,115 --> 00:21:23,917
I'll have it done today.

301
00:21:25,797 --> 00:21:29,601
How is he so quick and
always on top of everything?

302
00:21:29,601 --> 00:21:32,954
Well, there goes my excuse to put off quitting.

303
00:21:42,035 --> 00:21:44,370
[The following employee
will be converted to full-time.]

304
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:46,791
[Name: Woo Hyun Jin]

305
00:21:49,537 --> 00:21:51,503
Ms. Hyun Jin.

306
00:21:51,503 --> 00:21:54,292
Congrats on going full-time.

307
00:21:55,125 --> 00:21:57,163
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations.

308
00:21:57,163 --> 00:21:59,214
We'll be seeing you around a lot more now.

309
00:21:59,214 --> 00:22:01,047
- Looking forward to working with you.
- Congrats.

310
00:22:01,047 --> 00:22:02,232
Thank you.

311
00:22:02,232 --> 00:22:04,097
I'll work even harder from now on.

312
00:22:04,097 --> 00:22:06,981
Thank you for celebrating, everyone.

313
00:22:06,981 --> 00:22:09,354
Congratulations!

314
00:22:12,959 --> 00:22:13,983
This is so good.

315
00:22:13,983 --> 00:22:15,506
This place makes amazing cake.

316
00:22:15,506 --> 00:22:16,528
Right?

317
00:22:16,528 --> 00:22:19,490
I love their cakes.

318
00:22:20,371 --> 00:22:23,220
About you and the manager...

319
00:22:23,220 --> 00:22:25,490
Were you two pretty close back in college?

320
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:26,952
What?

321
00:22:26,952 --> 00:22:28,357
Actually,

322
00:22:28,357 --> 00:22:31,621
the manager insisted on
getting this chocolate cake.

323
00:22:31,621 --> 00:22:34,754
He even waited in line for it.

324
00:22:35,666 --> 00:22:37,168
From what I know,

325
00:22:37,168 --> 00:22:40,192
most guys don't remember stuff like that.

326
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,719
That's why you're single.

327
00:22:43,719 --> 00:22:45,719
Guys can be thoughtful too.

328
00:22:45,719 --> 00:22:47,764
If they care, they remember.

329
00:22:47,764 --> 00:22:49,583
Those are the ones who are popular

330
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:51,464
and actually good at dating.

331
00:22:51,464 --> 00:22:52,840
Hey, I'm popular too.

332
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:55,733
Yeah, Mr. Popular. Still single.

333
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:01,829
This is so good.

334
00:23:01,829 --> 00:23:04,402
Want another slice?

335
00:23:06,416 --> 00:23:08,276
Careful, you'll spill it.

336
00:23:08,276 --> 00:23:09,701
What's with your arm?

337
00:23:09,701 --> 00:23:11,247
Are you hurt?

338
00:23:11,247 --> 00:23:13,163
Oh gosh.

339
00:23:13,163 --> 00:23:14,747
That looks pretty bad.

340
00:23:14,747 --> 00:23:15,915
No, it's nothing.

341
00:23:15,915 --> 00:23:19,395
It just looks worse because of the bandage.

342
00:23:19,395 --> 00:23:21,501
I'm fine.

343
00:23:22,130 --> 00:23:25,296
What? Are you sure you're okay?

344
00:23:25,296 --> 00:23:27,414
See? I told you.

345
00:23:27,414 --> 00:23:30,545
That in-law was off from the start.

346
00:23:30,545 --> 00:23:31,823
What about here...

347
00:23:31,823 --> 00:23:33,641
Are you okay?

348
00:23:33,641 --> 00:23:37,074
It wasn't too bad. Thanks to Tae Hyung.

349
00:23:38,063 --> 00:23:41,566
We can't trust anyone these days...

350
00:23:41,566 --> 00:23:43,599
You must've been shaken up.

351
00:23:43,599 --> 00:23:47,092
Tae Hyung was probably more shaken than I was.

352
00:23:49,124 --> 00:23:50,983
But still...

353
00:23:50,983 --> 00:23:52,677
I can't stop thinking about it.

354
00:23:52,677 --> 00:23:54,514
What?

355
00:23:54,514 --> 00:23:55,789
Well...

356
00:23:55,789 --> 00:23:57,995
Maybe I shouldn't have gotten involved.

357
00:23:57,995 --> 00:24:00,168
This is partly my fault.

358
00:24:00,168 --> 00:24:02,170
Tae Hyung kept saying no,

359
00:24:02,170 --> 00:24:04,547
but I pushed him.

360
00:24:04,547 --> 00:24:05,757
I kept saying,

361
00:24:05,757 --> 00:24:08,676
"You can't just cut ties with your father."

362
00:24:08,676 --> 00:24:10,694
"He's still family. There has to be a reason."

363
00:24:10,694 --> 00:24:12,558
Stuff like that.

364
00:24:12,558 --> 00:24:14,265
Still...

365
00:24:14,265 --> 00:24:17,693
wouldn't it be better to at least
talk to him once?

366
00:24:17,693 --> 00:24:19,062
You think?

367
00:24:19,062 --> 00:24:20,563
Yeah.

368
00:24:20,563 --> 00:24:23,842
You and your in-law are still family.

369
00:24:23,842 --> 00:24:25,360
Especially when things are this hard,

370
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,189
you're supposed to lean on each other.

371
00:24:27,189 --> 00:24:29,076
Right?

372
00:24:31,639 --> 00:24:33,672
Yeah.

373
00:24:36,454 --> 00:24:38,627
Ms. Baek Se Yeon.

374
00:24:40,898 --> 00:24:42,344
Yes?

375
00:24:42,344 --> 00:24:45,092
Can I talk to you for a minute?

376
00:24:46,516 --> 00:24:48,469
Me?

377
00:24:49,292 --> 00:24:51,428
It's nothing serious.

378
00:24:51,428 --> 00:24:54,354
I just have a few questions.

379
00:24:56,141 --> 00:24:58,167
Do you happen to know

380
00:24:58,167 --> 00:25:00,931
what's going on with Hyun Jin's arm?

381
00:25:00,931 --> 00:25:01,938
Sorry?

382
00:25:01,938 --> 00:25:04,251
I was already worried

383
00:25:04,251 --> 00:25:05,817
when she took that day off.

384
00:25:05,817 --> 00:25:08,987
She said it was family stuff,
so I didn't press her.

385
00:25:08,987 --> 00:25:10,947
Did she get hurt that day?

386
00:25:10,947 --> 00:25:12,042
What happened?

387
00:25:13,211 --> 00:25:15,531
Well...

388
00:25:16,198 --> 00:25:17,871
That's kind of personal.

389
00:25:17,871 --> 00:25:19,539
I'm not sure I should say.

390
00:25:19,539 --> 00:25:21,958
I'm just worried.

391
00:25:21,958 --> 00:25:23,318
If I ask her,

392
00:25:23,318 --> 00:25:26,629
she'll say it's nothing.

393
00:25:26,629 --> 00:25:29,674
She's always looking out for everyone else,

394
00:25:29,674 --> 00:25:32,774
but never herself.

395
00:25:36,273 --> 00:25:39,406
I really shouldn't be telling you this...

396
00:25:42,696 --> 00:25:44,707
Your aunt is here.

397
00:25:44,707 --> 00:25:45,775
- Hey!
- Woo Joo's aunt.

398
00:25:45,775 --> 00:25:46,863
- It's Woo Joo's aunt.
- Hyun Jin.

399
00:25:46,863 --> 00:25:49,527
- Woo Joo's aunt.
- Hello.

400
00:25:49,527 --> 00:25:51,595
Woo Joo.

401
00:25:52,614 --> 00:25:56,868
That's why you can't judge a person
by how they look.

402
00:25:56,868 --> 00:25:59,245
I was completely fooled too.

403
00:25:59,245 --> 00:26:01,039
I know.

404
00:26:01,039 --> 00:26:03,416
We were shocked.

405
00:26:03,416 --> 00:26:04,542
I heard

406
00:26:04,542 --> 00:26:06,836
the one who broke into your place last time...

407
00:26:06,836 --> 00:26:08,546
that was Woo Joo's grandfather?

408
00:26:08,546 --> 00:26:10,882
I knew something was off.

409
00:26:10,882 --> 00:26:12,717
That thief they caught before

410
00:26:12,717 --> 00:26:15,810
didn't touch unit 206.

411
00:26:15,810 --> 00:26:17,263
And one time I saw that grandfather

412
00:26:17,263 --> 00:26:19,583
just standing there,

413
00:26:19,583 --> 00:26:22,771
staring at 206's door lock.

414
00:26:22,771 --> 00:26:24,358
No way.

415
00:26:24,358 --> 00:26:26,731
And here I was

416
00:26:26,731 --> 00:26:29,359
bad-mouthing Woo Joo's uncle,
saying he was cold.

417
00:26:29,359 --> 00:26:31,611
I feel awful now.

418
00:26:31,611 --> 00:26:34,257
You didn't know. It's understandable.

419
00:26:34,257 --> 00:26:37,457
So... how's Woo Joo's uncle doing?

420
00:26:37,457 --> 00:26:39,536
I saw him the other day...

421
00:26:39,536 --> 00:26:42,872
He didn't look well at all.

422
00:26:42,872 --> 00:26:44,225
Well, who wouldn't?

423
00:26:44,225 --> 00:26:45,708
It's not just anyone.

424
00:26:45,708 --> 00:26:47,627
His own father stabbed him in the back.

425
00:26:47,627 --> 00:26:49,200
I just can't believe this...

426
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:52,067
Maybe I should grab a drink with him.

427
00:26:52,067 --> 00:26:55,593
No, don't do that.

428
00:26:55,593 --> 00:26:59,697
Best thing right now is to leave him alone.

429
00:26:59,697 --> 00:27:01,641
That's what family is.

430
00:27:01,641 --> 00:27:04,802
It hurts when they're around,

431
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,620
and it hurts

432
00:27:07,620 --> 00:27:10,013
when they're gone.

433
00:27:26,462 --> 00:27:27,892
You're back.

434
00:27:27,892 --> 00:27:29,909
What's all this?

435
00:27:29,909 --> 00:27:32,802
Thought we could have a beer together.

436
00:27:36,365 --> 00:27:37,677
Where's Woo Joo?

437
00:27:37,677 --> 00:27:39,162
He's at Bom's place.

438
00:27:39,162 --> 00:27:41,830
Said he'd play a little longer with Ga Eul.

439
00:27:51,399 --> 00:27:54,277
You've been really busy lately, huh?

440
00:27:54,277 --> 00:27:57,139
Feels like you never get a day off.

441
00:27:58,402 --> 00:28:00,523
Just...

442
00:28:00,523 --> 00:28:03,297
work's been piling up.

443
00:28:03,297 --> 00:28:05,955
You've been having a hard time, haven't you?

444
00:28:05,955 --> 00:28:07,498
Ever since what happened

445
00:28:07,498 --> 00:28:10,081
with your father...

446
00:28:11,919 --> 00:28:14,797
If you need help, just tell me.

447
00:28:14,797 --> 00:28:16,549
When I was struggling at work,

448
00:28:16,549 --> 00:28:19,385
you were there for me.

449
00:28:19,385 --> 00:28:22,597
Don't keep it all bottled up.

450
00:28:22,597 --> 00:28:25,265
If it's hard, lean on me.

451
00:28:25,265 --> 00:28:26,709
We can do that much.

452
00:28:26,709 --> 00:28:28,829
We're family.

453
00:28:32,261 --> 00:28:34,414
Family?

454
00:28:36,694 --> 00:28:39,989
What do I even have like that?

455
00:28:39,989 --> 00:28:41,199
What?

456
00:28:41,199 --> 00:28:43,292
You saw it yourself.

457
00:28:45,411 --> 00:28:48,844
How my so-called family treats me.

458
00:28:49,791 --> 00:28:52,484
So don't talk to me about family.

459
00:28:54,170 --> 00:28:55,376
Hey,

460
00:28:55,376 --> 00:28:57,173
that's not fair.

461
00:28:57,173 --> 00:29:00,134
I know you're hurting
because of your father, but...

462
00:29:00,134 --> 00:29:01,886
What about me and Woo Joo?

463
00:29:01,886 --> 00:29:03,554
Aren't we your family?

464
00:29:03,554 --> 00:29:06,487
What even is family?

465
00:29:07,517 --> 00:29:10,228
The one who was supposed to be
my family walked away.

466
00:29:10,228 --> 00:29:13,022
I tried trusting him again,
and this is how it turned out.

467
00:29:13,022 --> 00:29:16,408
Now you got hurt too.

468
00:29:18,658 --> 00:29:20,678
If I'd never expected anything
in the first place,

469
00:29:20,678 --> 00:29:23,237
none of this would've happened.

470
00:29:32,792 --> 00:29:34,820
Thanks.

471
00:29:34,820 --> 00:29:37,107
And I'm sorry.

472
00:29:38,172 --> 00:29:40,945
I should get some rest.

473
00:30:11,419 --> 00:30:13,945
[Park Yoon Seong, BS Food]

474
00:30:28,014 --> 00:30:30,099
Why hasn't your uncle come by lately?

475
00:30:30,099 --> 00:30:31,476
Is he that busy with work?

476
00:30:31,476 --> 00:30:34,314
I never get to see him.

477
00:30:39,275 --> 00:30:41,368
Uncle...

478
00:30:47,786 --> 00:30:49,670
Here.

479
00:30:56,584 --> 00:30:57,710
Why?

480
00:30:57,710 --> 00:31:00,646
You have to eat a lot to grow big and strong.

481
00:31:00,646 --> 00:31:03,466
You used to eat so well when Tae Hyung made it.

482
00:31:03,466 --> 00:31:05,491
That's strange.

483
00:31:07,136 --> 00:31:09,347
Hey, what is it?

484
00:31:09,347 --> 00:31:10,848
If you do not eat this,

485
00:31:10,848 --> 00:31:14,322
I'm going to eat it all, okay?

486
00:31:21,943 --> 00:31:24,536
Just try this much.

487
00:31:32,817 --> 00:31:33,866
Fine.

488
00:31:33,866 --> 00:31:35,140
You don't want it?

489
00:31:36,243 --> 00:31:38,668
Okay. Then let's not eat.

490
00:31:38,668 --> 00:31:41,432
All done.

491
00:31:44,173 --> 00:31:45,508
Oh, seriously.

492
00:31:45,508 --> 00:31:47,728
Who is it?

493
00:31:47,728 --> 00:31:49,745
Hello?

494
00:31:49,745 --> 00:31:51,438
It's me.

495
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:55,226
[Manager Park Yoon Seong]

496
00:31:55,226 --> 00:31:56,227
Oh, Yoon Seong.

497
00:31:56,227 --> 00:31:57,503
What's up?

498
00:31:57,503 --> 00:31:59,438
Nothing much.

499
00:31:59,438 --> 00:32:00,982
Are you doing anything today?

500
00:32:00,982 --> 00:32:04,415
I was just going to hang out with Woo Joo.

501
00:32:05,069 --> 00:32:07,361
It's just the two of us at home.

502
00:32:09,198 --> 00:32:12,762
Would it be okay if I stopped by?

503
00:32:12,762 --> 00:32:14,579
I have something for Woo Joo.

504
00:32:14,579 --> 00:32:16,765
Right now?

505
00:32:19,876 --> 00:32:20,877
What's this?

506
00:32:20,877 --> 00:32:23,629
Apparently it's really popular
with kids these days.

507
00:32:23,629 --> 00:32:26,090
Oh, you didn't have to bring anything.

508
00:32:26,090 --> 00:32:27,927
It's a gift to celebrate you
becoming full-time.

509
00:32:27,927 --> 00:32:31,384
Think of it as a bonus from your manager.

510
00:32:31,384 --> 00:32:33,997
Yeah, thank you.

511
00:32:36,279 --> 00:32:39,046
I was feeding Woo Joo.

512
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:41,898
What about you?

513
00:32:41,898 --> 00:32:44,332
- Huh?
- Have you eaten?

514
00:32:44,332 --> 00:32:46,485
Not yet.

515
00:32:46,485 --> 00:32:50,225
How about we make today our second date?

516
00:33:15,681 --> 00:33:17,982
I just put something simple together
with what you had.

517
00:33:17,982 --> 00:33:20,486
The fried rice was already made.
I just touched it up a little.

518
00:33:21,715 --> 00:33:25,592
That's more than just "a little."

519
00:33:25,592 --> 00:33:29,085
How do you cook and clean as you go?

520
00:33:29,085 --> 00:33:31,822
You're full of surprises.

521
00:33:31,822 --> 00:33:33,991
I didn't think you were the domestic type.

522
00:33:33,991 --> 00:33:36,349
What exactly did you think of me?

523
00:33:36,349 --> 00:33:37,374
I mean...

524
00:33:37,374 --> 00:33:41,248
it's just really impressive.

525
00:33:41,248 --> 00:33:44,627
I've been doing this since I was young.

526
00:33:44,627 --> 00:33:45,883
Since you were young?

527
00:33:45,883 --> 00:33:47,755
Cooking and taking care of the house?

528
00:33:47,755 --> 00:33:49,780
Really?

529
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:53,236
Looks like I nailed Woo Joo's taste.

530
00:33:57,263 --> 00:33:59,596
Woo Joo.

531
00:34:00,243 --> 00:34:01,774
Give it to me.

532
00:34:01,774 --> 00:34:04,362
Good job, dear.

533
00:34:05,773 --> 00:34:07,024
Hi, Woo Joo.

534
00:34:07,024 --> 00:34:09,573
Should we defeat the bad guy?

535
00:34:09,573 --> 00:34:11,001
Is that yours?

536
00:34:11,001 --> 00:34:13,090
Bad guy!

537
00:34:22,081 --> 00:34:23,499
It's stuck on, Woo Joo.

538
00:34:23,499 --> 00:34:25,634
What's this?

539
00:34:50,151 --> 00:34:52,451
Want to try blowing this?

540
00:34:53,468 --> 00:34:54,780
You're...

541
00:34:54,780 --> 00:34:57,783
actually pretty good with kids.

542
00:34:57,783 --> 00:35:00,176
I had quite a few younger kids around me.

543
00:35:00,176 --> 00:35:03,115
Guess I'm finally putting

544
00:35:03,115 --> 00:35:04,668
those skills to use.

545
00:35:04,668 --> 00:35:06,959
Younger kids?

546
00:35:06,959 --> 00:35:10,588
I thought you were an only child.

547
00:35:10,588 --> 00:35:12,988
I am.

548
00:35:13,859 --> 00:35:17,332
I was adopted. In middle school.

549
00:35:19,736 --> 00:35:21,766
When I was at the children's home,

550
00:35:21,766 --> 00:35:25,227
it was my job to play with the younger kids.

551
00:35:25,227 --> 00:35:26,812
I was...

552
00:35:26,812 --> 00:35:29,745
pretty popular with them.

553
00:35:31,243 --> 00:35:33,130
Are you surprised?

554
00:35:33,130 --> 00:35:34,361
No.

555
00:35:34,361 --> 00:35:36,822
Not surprised...

556
00:35:36,822 --> 00:35:39,033
I just didn't know.

557
00:35:39,033 --> 00:35:42,411
It's not a big deal to me anymore.

558
00:35:42,411 --> 00:35:45,831
I wasn't trying to hide it.

559
00:35:45,831 --> 00:35:48,564
It just never came up.

560
00:35:52,213 --> 00:35:54,993
You really are the lucky one.

561
00:35:56,166 --> 00:35:59,220
Seeing how strong and grounded you turned out,

562
00:35:59,220 --> 00:36:02,898
your parents must be wonderful people.

563
00:36:03,684 --> 00:36:06,417
That's the real privilege.

564
00:36:07,328 --> 00:36:08,896
Yeah.

565
00:36:08,896 --> 00:36:11,069
Hyun Jin.

566
00:36:11,982 --> 00:36:15,029
That's why I'm confident.

567
00:36:16,028 --> 00:36:19,156
I was lucky to meet a good family

568
00:36:19,156 --> 00:36:22,029
and grow up surrounded by love.

569
00:36:23,266 --> 00:36:26,061
So I know, better than anyone,

570
00:36:26,061 --> 00:36:28,791
how to give love.

571
00:36:28,791 --> 00:36:30,730
I don't think

572
00:36:30,730 --> 00:36:34,104
family has to look a certain way.

573
00:36:35,548 --> 00:36:36,715
So...

574
00:36:36,715 --> 00:36:39,301
I can be a steady umbrella

575
00:36:39,301 --> 00:36:42,394
for you and for Woo Joo.

576
00:36:43,246 --> 00:36:45,432
No matter how hard it storms,

577
00:36:45,432 --> 00:36:49,120
I'll stand firm and protect you.

578
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:51,921
If you'll let me.

579
00:37:16,758 --> 00:37:18,674
I heard everything.

580
00:37:18,674 --> 00:37:22,943
About what happened to Hyun Jin's arm.

581
00:37:24,221 --> 00:37:27,516
You said she is family, right?

582
00:37:27,516 --> 00:37:29,291
You said there was nothing to worry about.

583
00:37:29,291 --> 00:37:32,146
Then what is this?

584
00:37:32,146 --> 00:37:34,099
Again, you said she is family.

585
00:37:34,099 --> 00:37:37,601
How could you put your own family
in that kind of danger?

586
00:37:37,601 --> 00:37:39,658
How many times has Hyun Jin been put at risk

587
00:37:39,658 --> 00:37:43,168
because of you?

588
00:37:43,168 --> 00:37:45,117
I honestly don't know anymore.

589
00:37:45,117 --> 00:37:49,030
Whether you are truly acting like family...

590
00:37:49,030 --> 00:37:52,725
or just making her life harder.

591
00:38:07,852 --> 00:38:10,059
Tae Hyung.

592
00:38:14,104 --> 00:38:16,815
I'm really not doing well right now.

593
00:38:16,815 --> 00:38:19,190
Please give me some inmate funds.

594
00:38:19,190 --> 00:38:21,487
Let me be clear.

595
00:38:21,487 --> 00:38:24,198
There will be no settlement. No leniency.

596
00:38:24,198 --> 00:38:26,024
You...

597
00:38:26,024 --> 00:38:27,810
How could you say that to your own father?

598
00:38:27,810 --> 00:38:30,093
If you...

599
00:38:31,705 --> 00:38:35,305
If you were human,
you never should have done that.

600
00:38:36,335 --> 00:38:38,303
My brother...

601
00:38:39,134 --> 00:38:44,126
What did that child ever do to you
to deserve what you did to him?

602
00:38:44,777 --> 00:38:46,845
And you still call yourself a father?

603
00:38:46,845 --> 00:38:49,645
Do you even have the right?

604
00:38:49,645 --> 00:38:51,338
What you did to my brother wasn't enough,

605
00:38:51,338 --> 00:38:53,258
so you had to drag me down to rock bottom too?

606
00:38:53,258 --> 00:38:56,021
I don't know what you've heard,

607
00:38:56,021 --> 00:38:58,693
but I had my reasons.

608
00:38:58,693 --> 00:39:01,337
You're shameless.

609
00:39:01,337 --> 00:39:03,546
Yeah.

610
00:39:03,546 --> 00:39:06,615
That's exactly like you.

611
00:39:06,615 --> 00:39:09,108
From now on,

612
00:39:09,702 --> 00:39:11,829
I'm going to live as if I don't have a family.

613
00:39:11,829 --> 00:39:14,549
So consider this a warning.

614
00:39:15,666 --> 00:39:19,749
Make sure I never see your face again.

615
00:39:19,749 --> 00:39:23,302
- What?
- From this point on...

616
00:39:23,924 --> 00:39:26,690
you and I are finished.

617
00:39:27,845 --> 00:39:31,689
I've already filed for a restraining order.
If you ever...

618
00:39:32,866 --> 00:39:34,893
show up in front of Woo Joo or Hyun Jin again,

619
00:39:34,893 --> 00:39:36,998
then...

620
00:39:38,397 --> 00:39:41,477
Then I won't hold back.

621
00:39:44,086 --> 00:39:45,526
Tae Hyung.

622
00:39:45,526 --> 00:39:46,739
Tae Hyung.

623
00:39:46,739 --> 00:39:48,932
Tae Hyung!

624
00:40:04,344 --> 00:40:07,088
[The late Sun Woo Jin]
[The late Woo Hyun Joo]

625
00:40:09,850 --> 00:40:11,555
[Sun Woo Jin]

626
00:40:11,555 --> 00:40:14,581
I'm here, bro.

627
00:40:16,057 --> 00:40:18,798
I'm so late.

628
00:40:21,648 --> 00:40:25,301
I only just realized
you protected me to the very end.

629
00:40:27,469 --> 00:40:30,363
And that you loved me.

630
00:40:33,994 --> 00:40:36,296
I'm sorry.

631
00:40:39,166 --> 00:40:41,759
I'm so sorry.

632
00:41:01,784 --> 00:41:02,819
Sun Woo Joo.

633
00:41:02,819 --> 00:41:03,962
Woo Joo,

634
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:06,131
your uncle's here to pick you up today.

635
00:41:06,131 --> 00:41:07,257
Put your shoes on.

636
00:41:07,257 --> 00:41:08,656
Uncle!

637
00:41:08,656 --> 00:41:10,802
Yeah? Did you miss me?

638
00:41:10,802 --> 00:41:12,015
- Sun Woo Joo.
- He must be excited...

639
00:41:12,015 --> 00:41:13,596
since it's been a while.

640
00:41:13,596 --> 00:41:14,889
Right, Woo Joo?

641
00:41:14,889 --> 00:41:17,050
Uncle Tae Hyung.

642
00:41:17,050 --> 00:41:18,977
That's right. Uncle Tae Hyung.

643
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:21,530
Uncle Tae Hyung.

644
00:41:41,666 --> 00:41:43,418
You're back?

645
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:45,951
I was just waiting for you.

646
00:41:47,445 --> 00:41:48,590
Really?

647
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:50,383
You could've called.

648
00:41:50,383 --> 00:41:52,760
Where's Woo Joo?

649
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:55,556
He just fell asleep.

650
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:01,811
What's all this?

651
00:42:01,811 --> 00:42:04,224
Are you going somewhere?

652
00:42:09,078 --> 00:42:10,778
Yeah.

653
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:13,198
It's time for me to go home.

654
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:15,074
What?

655
00:42:15,074 --> 00:42:17,902
Go where?

656
00:42:17,902 --> 00:42:21,083
I lied to you.

657
00:42:21,915 --> 00:42:24,921
My place has been finished for a while.

658
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:30,173
Is this because of that?

659
00:42:30,173 --> 00:42:31,591
Because of your father?

660
00:42:31,591 --> 00:42:33,787
No.

661
00:42:33,787 --> 00:42:35,728
We agreed from the start

662
00:42:35,728 --> 00:42:38,652
it would only be for a month.

663
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,823
It's time for me to leave.

664
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:45,936
Tae Hyung...

665
00:42:46,689 --> 00:42:48,659
I know you're doing this

666
00:42:48,659 --> 00:42:50,777
because you feel guilty toward me.

667
00:42:50,777 --> 00:42:52,487
But we're family.

668
00:42:52,487 --> 00:42:54,489
Especially at times like this, family should...

669
00:42:54,489 --> 00:42:56,115
Family. Family.

670
00:42:56,115 --> 00:42:58,868
What does that even mean?

671
00:42:58,868 --> 00:43:00,495
I've never had a family.

672
00:43:00,495 --> 00:43:02,693
I don't even know how.

673
00:43:02,693 --> 00:43:03,732
Hey...

674
00:43:03,732 --> 00:43:05,025
You've seen my father.

675
00:43:05,025 --> 00:43:08,072
You know what kind of man he is.

676
00:43:08,962 --> 00:43:11,482
I'm his son.

677
00:43:11,482 --> 00:43:15,135
That's the kind of family I come from.

678
00:43:16,302 --> 00:43:18,153
I grew up

679
00:43:18,153 --> 00:43:20,165
without ever really being loved.

680
00:43:20,165 --> 00:43:21,754
So I went my whole life

681
00:43:21,754 --> 00:43:24,854
not even knowing when someone was loving me.

682
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:28,898
And someone like that is
supposed to be "family?"

683
00:43:28,898 --> 00:43:30,567
You have to learn that somewhere

684
00:43:30,567 --> 00:43:32,151
to even pretend to do it.

685
00:43:32,151 --> 00:43:34,529
We can figure it out together.

686
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:36,681
Like we have been. The two of us...

687
00:43:36,681 --> 00:43:38,266
I thought...

688
00:43:38,266 --> 00:43:41,217
I thought maybe I could try

689
00:43:41,217 --> 00:43:44,147
this whole "family" thing.

690
00:43:46,207 --> 00:43:48,833
But I don't think I can.

691
00:43:49,983 --> 00:43:54,007
I can't even protect one person properly.

692
00:43:54,007 --> 00:43:56,200
I don't know how to love someone the right way.

693
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:58,637
How can I have a family?

694
00:43:59,462 --> 00:44:02,223
And honestly...

695
00:44:02,223 --> 00:44:04,183
Woo Joo

696
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:07,103
and you.

697
00:44:07,103 --> 00:44:09,939
I'm not ready to take responsibility
for either of you.

698
00:44:09,939 --> 00:44:11,174
I can barely take care of myself.

699
00:44:11,174 --> 00:44:14,280
How am I supposed to take care of anyone else?

700
00:44:16,110 --> 00:44:19,282
I'm not asking you
to take responsibility for us.

701
00:44:19,282 --> 00:44:21,563
Do you think I'm doing this
because I'm confident?

702
00:44:21,563 --> 00:44:22,602
I'm not.

703
00:44:22,602 --> 00:44:25,525
I've never done this before either.

704
00:44:26,122 --> 00:44:30,515
But I'm trying
because I want things to work with you.

705
00:44:31,114 --> 00:44:32,641
You can't even see that?

706
00:44:32,641 --> 00:44:35,994
Then don't try for me.

707
00:44:40,249 --> 00:44:44,502
Later, when you get hurt because of me,
I don't want you to regret it.

708
00:44:45,808 --> 00:44:48,821
Let's just stop.

709
00:45:39,487 --> 00:45:41,489
Woo Joo.

710
00:45:41,489 --> 00:45:44,784
You know...

711
00:45:44,784 --> 00:45:48,204
I don't think I can live with you anymore.

712
00:45:48,204 --> 00:45:51,683
I'm not ready.

713
00:45:51,683 --> 00:45:53,418
Not ready?

714
00:45:53,418 --> 00:45:55,998
I don't have the courage.

715
00:45:57,255 --> 00:45:59,549
Like your dad did...

716
00:46:01,134 --> 00:46:04,303
I'm scared your aunt might get hurt

717
00:46:04,303 --> 00:46:07,123
because of me.

718
00:46:07,123 --> 00:46:10,463
But no matter what,
I'm still your uncle, right?

719
00:46:11,602 --> 00:46:14,480
Even if we don't live together,

720
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:17,734
I'll still come see you a lot,

721
00:46:17,734 --> 00:46:21,904
and I'll take you fun places too.

722
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:24,190
- Okay?
- Okay.

723
00:46:25,641 --> 00:46:27,815
So yeah,

724
00:46:28,953 --> 00:46:31,038
even for a second,

725
00:46:31,038 --> 00:46:32,524
don't ever think

726
00:46:32,524 --> 00:46:35,905
that I abandoned you.

727
00:46:59,192 --> 00:47:00,943
Got your socks on...

728
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:02,403
Done!

729
00:47:02,403 --> 00:47:04,197
Wait a second.

730
00:47:04,197 --> 00:47:06,741
Let me grab a handkerchief.

731
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:10,203
Alright, handkerchief in.

732
00:47:10,203 --> 00:47:12,330
Lunchbox in.

733
00:47:12,330 --> 00:47:14,243
Water.

734
00:47:18,906 --> 00:47:20,074
[Make sure you eat some toast before you go.]
[Okay.]

735
00:47:20,074 --> 00:47:21,698
[Lunch duty for Woo Joo: done!]

736
00:47:21,698 --> 00:47:23,452
[I'm working late tonight.]
[Hang in there!]

737
00:47:29,138 --> 00:47:30,723
Woo Joo, let's go.

738
00:47:30,723 --> 00:47:33,084
We're late.

739
00:47:33,084 --> 00:47:34,811
You skipped breakfast again, didn't you?

740
00:47:34,811 --> 00:47:36,687
At least eat this and take your medicine.

741
00:47:36,687 --> 00:47:40,533
Even if you hate hot drinks,
don't drink cold water.

742
00:47:43,653 --> 00:47:45,259
I heard from the lawyer yesterday.

743
00:47:45,259 --> 00:47:48,574
You said you'd just sign?

744
00:47:48,574 --> 00:47:49,700
Yeah.

745
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:50,747
Why?

746
00:47:50,747 --> 00:47:54,148
I thought you were going to sue
over the settlement.

747
00:47:54,148 --> 00:47:56,227
Sue? No.

748
00:47:57,375 --> 00:47:59,752
You're basically a celebrity, you know?

749
00:47:59,752 --> 00:48:01,295
If the lawsuit drags on,

750
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:03,666
people are going to start talking.

751
00:48:03,666 --> 00:48:05,074
You know how that goes.

752
00:48:05,074 --> 00:48:08,232
Then when are you quitting?

753
00:48:08,232 --> 00:48:09,287
What?

754
00:48:09,287 --> 00:48:11,998
You're getting divorced soon,
and you've already finished the handover.

755
00:48:11,998 --> 00:48:14,963
There's no reason for you to keep coming in.

756
00:48:14,963 --> 00:48:16,894
Yeah, I will quit soon.

757
00:48:16,894 --> 00:48:19,438
But you think it ends with a handover?

758
00:48:19,438 --> 00:48:21,423
I stayed to make sure

759
00:48:21,423 --> 00:48:23,234
Sun Tae Hyung adjusts properly.

760
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:26,600
So stop worrying and just wrap things up.

761
00:48:31,365 --> 00:48:32,410
I'm sorry, sir.

762
00:48:32,410 --> 00:48:35,788
I get carsick, so I can't sit in the front.

763
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:36,956
That's okay.

764
00:48:36,956 --> 00:48:38,749
I actually prefer the front seat.

765
00:48:38,749 --> 00:48:40,418
By the way, Ms. Hyun Jin,

766
00:48:40,418 --> 00:48:43,178
are you sure you're okay driving
the whole way by yourself?

767
00:48:43,178 --> 00:48:44,797
Of course. Don't worry.

768
00:48:44,797 --> 00:48:46,757
Everyone, try to get some sleep.

769
00:48:46,757 --> 00:48:48,676
Today's shoot might run long.

770
00:48:48,676 --> 00:48:50,303
Oh, come on.

771
00:48:50,303 --> 00:48:53,598
How can we sleep comfortably
with you right here, sir?

772
00:48:53,598 --> 00:48:54,974
Exactly.

773
00:48:54,974 --> 00:48:58,487
We'd feel too awkward to sleep.

774
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:07,987
If you get tired, let me know.

775
00:49:07,987 --> 00:49:09,447
I can drive.

776
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:11,657
Okay, I will.

777
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:13,326
You should get some rest too.

778
00:49:13,326 --> 00:49:15,965
We've still got a long way to go.

779
00:49:15,965 --> 00:49:17,092
Oh, wait.

780
00:49:17,092 --> 00:49:18,798
What's this?

781
00:49:18,798 --> 00:49:21,334
I packed some snacks for the team.

782
00:49:21,334 --> 00:49:24,128
I figured no one had breakfast.

783
00:49:24,128 --> 00:49:25,571
Help yourself.

784
00:49:25,571 --> 00:49:27,937
There's plenty.

785
00:49:35,540 --> 00:49:37,767
Hey...

786
00:49:37,767 --> 00:49:39,712
You look like you barely slept.

787
00:49:39,712 --> 00:49:41,687
I don't want you dozing off while driving.

788
00:49:41,687 --> 00:49:44,107
Come on, open up.

789
00:49:45,938 --> 00:49:48,064
Thank you.

790
00:50:07,415 --> 00:50:09,674
You can stand right here.

791
00:50:09,674 --> 00:50:12,642
If you look at today's storyboard...

792
00:50:14,152 --> 00:50:15,718
We're going for a really natural feel.

793
00:50:15,718 --> 00:50:17,640
Just scoop the gochujang like that.

794
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,725
Please just watch your expression,
maybe like this.

795
00:50:19,725 --> 00:50:21,394
Got it.

796
00:50:21,394 --> 00:50:23,604
Please slick the hair all the way back.

797
00:50:23,604 --> 00:50:26,244
Manager, here is the storyboard.

798
00:50:28,192 --> 00:50:30,152
Did you check it?

799
00:50:30,152 --> 00:50:31,212
Yeah.

800
00:50:31,212 --> 00:50:33,764
The mise-en-scène is killer.

801
00:50:33,764 --> 00:50:36,198
Have some coffee, everyone.

802
00:50:36,198 --> 00:50:38,481
Thank you.

803
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:47,135
He's good.

804
00:51:03,853 --> 00:51:06,366
I'm telling you, it's real.

805
00:51:06,366 --> 00:51:08,649
Can't you see the vibe between those two?

806
00:51:08,649 --> 00:51:11,024
They are one hundred percent dating.

807
00:51:11,024 --> 00:51:13,571
I saw it in the car earlier.

808
00:51:13,571 --> 00:51:16,628
They were feeding each other candy.

809
00:51:16,628 --> 00:51:17,658
Really?

810
00:51:17,658 --> 00:51:18,909
Lucky her.

811
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:20,411
She totally hit the jackpot.

812
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:22,455
Honestly, where do you find a guy
like our manager?

813
00:51:22,455 --> 00:51:24,331
Education, skills, money, family...

814
00:51:24,331 --> 00:51:26,640
He's got it all.

815
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:28,085
- Right?
- So jealous.

816
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:29,279
- Seung Taek.
- Yes?

817
00:51:29,279 --> 00:51:31,255
The natural light's good right now.
Let's keep it.

818
00:51:31,255 --> 00:51:32,339
No bounce.

819
00:51:32,339 --> 00:51:33,544
Got it.

820
00:51:33,544 --> 00:51:35,921
We'll adjust the lighting and go right in.

821
00:51:35,921 --> 00:51:37,762
For his first shoot,

822
00:51:37,762 --> 00:51:39,555
Tae Hyung isn't even nervous.

823
00:51:39,555 --> 00:51:41,928
He's a natural.

824
00:51:56,974 --> 00:52:00,250
Did you check the spot from the draft?

825
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:01,753
Yes.

826
00:52:01,753 --> 00:52:04,187
It's that center line on the stairs.

827
00:52:04,187 --> 00:52:06,646
Up there, right?

828
00:52:19,860 --> 00:52:23,561
This won't even need much retouching.

829
00:52:23,561 --> 00:52:24,892
What do you think?

830
00:52:24,892 --> 00:52:26,085
Looks good.

831
00:52:26,085 --> 00:52:29,258
- Nice, right?
- Yeah, it's good.

832
00:52:41,200 --> 00:52:42,660
How's the setup?

833
00:52:42,660 --> 00:52:45,513
If it looks good, should we go with this?

834
00:52:46,789 --> 00:52:48,332
It might look more appetizing.

835
00:52:48,332 --> 00:52:49,494
Yeah, I like it.

836
00:52:49,494 --> 00:52:52,301
Sir, what do you think?

837
00:53:02,847 --> 00:53:04,181
Good. Let's go with this.

838
00:53:04,181 --> 00:53:05,545
Rolling!

839
00:53:05,545 --> 00:53:07,577
Okay.

840
00:53:07,577 --> 00:53:09,563
Oh my!

841
00:53:14,759 --> 00:53:15,788
- Sir!
- Hyun Jin.

842
00:53:15,788 --> 00:53:16,968
- Are you okay?
- Manager...

843
00:53:16,968 --> 00:53:18,127
Hyun Jin, you okay?

844
00:53:18,127 --> 00:53:20,364
Are you okay?

845
00:53:20,364 --> 00:53:23,070
Oh no.

846
00:53:23,070 --> 00:53:25,077
Are you okay?

847
00:53:25,077 --> 00:53:27,117
Get up.

848
00:53:30,666 --> 00:53:32,793
Shouldn't you go to the hospital?

849
00:53:32,793 --> 00:53:34,232
- I'm fine.
- No, you're not.

850
00:53:34,232 --> 00:53:36,547
Sir, you need to put something on that.

851
00:53:36,547 --> 00:53:37,948
Ms. Hyun Jin, let's treat yours too.

852
00:53:37,948 --> 00:53:38,988
Come here.

853
00:53:38,988 --> 00:53:40,997
You need ointment.

854
00:53:44,247 --> 00:53:46,974
Hurry, hurry.

855
00:53:46,974 --> 00:53:48,809
Where's the first-aid kit?

856
00:53:48,809 --> 00:53:51,569
First-aid kit, please. Quickly.

857
00:53:57,651 --> 00:54:00,738
Why did you jump in there like that?

858
00:54:00,738 --> 00:54:04,018
Are you really okay?

859
00:54:05,492 --> 00:54:09,288
What, you're smiling right now?

860
00:54:09,288 --> 00:54:12,499
It's just a scrape. It's nothing.

861
00:54:12,499 --> 00:54:14,667
You were scared, huh?

862
00:54:15,961 --> 00:54:18,214
Me too.

863
00:54:18,214 --> 00:54:19,866
That look in your eyes is scary.

864
00:54:19,866 --> 00:54:22,872
I told you, I'm fine.

865
00:54:23,677 --> 00:54:27,022
Thank you so much.

866
00:54:29,722 --> 00:54:32,019
The pictures turned out great.

867
00:54:32,019 --> 00:54:33,229
Right?

868
00:54:33,229 --> 00:54:36,023
Is Manager Park okay?

869
00:54:36,023 --> 00:54:38,484
Thankfully, it wasn't serious.

870
00:54:38,484 --> 00:54:40,486
That scared me.

871
00:54:40,486 --> 00:54:42,249
That could've been really bad.

872
00:54:42,249 --> 00:54:43,989
Maybe it's because he's young.

873
00:54:43,989 --> 00:54:45,991
How does he just jump in like that
without thinking?

874
00:54:45,991 --> 00:54:48,118
It's not about being young.

875
00:54:48,118 --> 00:54:50,062
It's about the heart.

876
00:54:50,062 --> 00:54:51,088
"Heart?"

877
00:54:51,088 --> 00:54:54,667
In that split second,
he threw himself in there.

878
00:54:54,667 --> 00:54:57,753
His body moved
before he even had time to think.

879
00:54:57,753 --> 00:54:59,004
To protect Ms. Hyun Jin.

880
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:01,877
Protect her? Why?

881
00:55:07,079 --> 00:55:10,099
Come on, you're talking like
you know everything.

882
00:55:10,099 --> 00:55:12,309
What do you mean I don't know?

883
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:14,103
There's no one here who knows better than I do.

884
00:55:14,103 --> 00:55:15,502
You don't know a thing.

885
00:55:15,502 --> 00:55:16,522
Look.

886
00:55:16,522 --> 00:55:18,065
It's obvious Hyun Jin looks better

887
00:55:18,065 --> 00:55:19,854
with Sun Tae Hyung.

888
00:55:19,854 --> 00:55:21,661
What are you talking about?

889
00:55:21,661 --> 00:55:24,696
She clearly matches our manager better.

890
00:55:24,696 --> 00:55:26,017
What?

891
00:55:26,017 --> 00:55:27,074
No way.

892
00:55:27,074 --> 00:55:29,489
Just look at them together.
The chemistry is obvious.

893
00:55:29,489 --> 00:55:31,620
No, it's not.

894
00:55:31,620 --> 00:55:33,998
She has way better chemistry with our manager.

895
00:55:33,998 --> 00:55:37,997
Oh my, you really have no eye for this.

896
00:55:39,578 --> 00:55:41,972
Gyu Jeong, you've never dated anyone, right?

897
00:55:41,972 --> 00:55:45,197
- What?
- Yeah, you totally haven't.

898
00:55:45,197 --> 00:55:47,250
Never dated.

899
00:55:48,095 --> 00:55:49,972
So what if I'm single? What's wrong with that?

900
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:52,850
Not single. Never dated.

901
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:55,176
I'm single by choice.

902
00:55:55,176 --> 00:55:57,663
You know? I'm married.

903
00:55:57,663 --> 00:56:00,149
So I've got a sharp eye for couples.

904
00:56:00,149 --> 00:56:02,662
I'm very popular, you know!

905
00:56:10,492 --> 00:56:13,704
In that split second,
he threw himself in there.

906
00:56:13,704 --> 00:56:16,498
His body moved
before he even had time to think.

907
00:56:16,498 --> 00:56:17,624
To protect Ms. Hyun Jin.

908
00:56:17,624 --> 00:56:19,585
Honestly, where do you find a guy
like our manager?

909
00:56:19,585 --> 00:56:21,295
Education, skills, money, family...

910
00:56:21,295 --> 00:56:23,975
He's got it all.

911
00:56:31,972 --> 00:56:33,390
This is basically brand new.

912
00:56:33,390 --> 00:56:34,805
Can I really take it?

913
00:56:34,805 --> 00:56:36,810
Yeah.

914
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:40,249
It was just taking up space in storage.

915
00:56:40,249 --> 00:56:42,524
I was about to get rid of it anyway.

916
00:56:42,524 --> 00:56:44,913
Well, I'm not complaining.

917
00:56:44,913 --> 00:56:47,279
But are you going to keep living here?

918
00:56:47,279 --> 00:56:48,697
What about you?

919
00:56:48,697 --> 00:56:51,827
Did you really move out for good?

920
00:56:51,827 --> 00:56:54,930
You didn't have to leave the house.

921
00:56:57,012 --> 00:56:58,957
I just...

922
00:56:58,957 --> 00:57:01,293
felt like I could not face Hyun Jin.

923
00:57:01,293 --> 00:57:02,795
Why?

924
00:57:02,795 --> 00:57:05,488
Because of what happened that day?

925
00:57:05,488 --> 00:57:07,628
You know...

926
00:57:07,628 --> 00:57:09,846
After her sister passed like that,

927
00:57:09,846 --> 00:57:12,946
she had a really hard time.

928
00:57:12,946 --> 00:57:16,517
She could not even go

929
00:57:16,517 --> 00:57:18,830
into the bedroom alone.

930
00:57:21,163 --> 00:57:23,524
And if you really think about it...

931
00:57:23,524 --> 00:57:26,026
it happened because of me.

932
00:57:26,026 --> 00:57:27,778
So, your in-law...

933
00:57:27,778 --> 00:57:31,251
she doesn't know about
you and your brother yet, right?

934
00:57:32,022 --> 00:57:33,614
She can't.

935
00:57:33,614 --> 00:57:36,078
If she finds out, she'll worry.

936
00:57:36,078 --> 00:57:39,456
But are you really okay with this?

937
00:57:39,456 --> 00:57:42,162
You like her.

938
00:57:45,087 --> 00:57:47,398
How do you...

939
00:57:47,398 --> 00:57:49,478
know that?

940
00:57:49,478 --> 00:57:51,885
Come on. I've known you for years.

941
00:57:51,885 --> 00:57:54,526
You think I wouldn't notice?

942
00:57:56,056 --> 00:57:58,593
Yeah, I like her.

943
00:57:59,515 --> 00:58:01,562
But maybe...

944
00:58:01,562 --> 00:58:05,282
wouldn't it be better to just stay by her side?

945
00:58:09,778 --> 00:58:11,655
I don't know.

946
00:58:11,655 --> 00:58:14,859
Would me being there even help?

947
00:58:17,536 --> 00:58:19,021
Anyone can see it.

948
00:58:19,021 --> 00:58:21,540
There's already someone better than me

949
00:58:21,540 --> 00:58:23,706
by her side.

950
00:58:26,110 --> 00:58:28,508
Maybe...

951
00:58:28,508 --> 00:58:30,424
If I care about her,

952
00:58:30,424 --> 00:58:33,260
I should just hope

953
00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:35,886
she ends up with someone like that.

954
00:58:39,082 --> 00:58:41,226
- Your aunt's here.
- Hello.

955
00:58:41,226 --> 00:58:43,562
Woo Joo.

956
00:58:43,562 --> 00:58:45,564
Sorry, I'm really late.

957
00:58:45,564 --> 00:58:47,191
My meeting ran way over.

958
00:58:47,191 --> 00:58:50,360
It's okay, that happens when you're working.

959
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:52,154
By the way,

960
00:58:52,154 --> 00:58:54,865
I heard you and Woo Joo's uncle
are living apart now.

961
00:58:54,865 --> 00:58:56,882
Is that true?

962
00:58:58,118 --> 00:59:00,662
Yeah... that's how it ended up.

963
00:59:00,662 --> 00:59:03,808
You two didn't have a fight, did you?

964
00:59:05,209 --> 00:59:06,850
No.

965
00:59:06,850 --> 00:59:09,796
Well, don't go fighting.

966
00:59:09,796 --> 00:59:12,914
You two working things out together

967
00:59:12,914 --> 00:59:14,243
and raising Woo Joo,

968
00:59:14,243 --> 00:59:17,653
that was such a good thing to see.

969
00:59:17,653 --> 00:59:19,181
Oh, right.

970
00:59:19,181 --> 00:59:23,127
I heard Woo Joo's daycare is...

971
00:59:23,127 --> 00:59:25,559
having a recital.

972
00:59:25,559 --> 00:59:29,191
You should call him and go together.

973
00:59:31,818 --> 00:59:33,529
You learned that today?

974
00:59:33,529 --> 00:59:34,947
It was fun.

975
00:59:34,947 --> 00:59:38,753
Looks like you ate well today.

976
00:59:38,753 --> 00:59:40,630
What's this?

977
00:59:40,630 --> 00:59:42,437
[Saetbyeol Daycare]

978
00:59:43,522 --> 00:59:44,593
[You're Invited]

979
00:59:44,593 --> 00:59:48,460
I heard Woo Joo's daycare is having a recital.

980
00:59:48,460 --> 00:59:51,547
You should call him and go together.

981
00:59:51,547 --> 00:59:52,756
From what I hear,

982
00:59:52,756 --> 00:59:56,900
even the grandparents are all showing up.

983
01:00:02,589 --> 01:00:04,835
[Temporary helper]

984
01:00:07,380 --> 01:00:09,180
[Temporary helper]

985
01:00:10,880 --> 01:00:12,985
Fine.

986
01:00:12,985 --> 01:00:14,247
It's just a recital.

987
01:00:15,571 --> 01:00:17,447
Did you practice today, Woo Joo?

988
01:00:17,447 --> 01:00:18,239
Yeah.

989
01:00:18,239 --> 01:00:20,325
Really?

990
01:00:20,325 --> 01:00:21,868
[Saetbyeol Daycare Annual Recital]
Say hello to your teacher.

991
01:00:21,868 --> 01:00:23,161
Hello.

992
01:00:23,161 --> 01:00:24,466
You'll do great today, right?

993
01:00:24,466 --> 01:00:25,356
[Saetbyeol Daycare Little Stars]
Come here.

994
01:00:25,356 --> 01:00:27,082
Let's take a picture. Come here.

995
01:00:27,082 --> 01:00:28,766
Could you take a photo for us?

996
01:00:28,766 --> 01:00:31,312
[Saetbyeol Daycare Little Stars]
Picture time. One, two...

997
01:00:56,915 --> 01:01:00,222
Maybe I should've brought a bigger bouquet.

998
01:01:02,242 --> 01:01:04,494
Hyun Jin.

999
01:01:04,494 --> 01:01:05,662
Oh, hello.

1000
01:01:05,662 --> 01:01:07,623
Why are you just standing there?

1001
01:01:07,623 --> 01:01:09,782
I came because I heard it was a recital,

1002
01:01:09,782 --> 01:01:11,485
but I didn't realize it would be this big.

1003
01:01:11,485 --> 01:01:13,837
This must be your first time.

1004
01:01:13,837 --> 01:01:17,341
I should've given you a heads-up.

1005
01:01:17,341 --> 01:01:18,717
Where's Woo Joo's uncle?

1006
01:01:18,717 --> 01:01:20,052
Didn't he come with you?

1007
01:01:20,052 --> 01:01:23,165
You should've come together.

1008
01:01:24,645 --> 01:01:26,183
I know.

1009
01:01:26,183 --> 01:01:28,419
Mom, take my picture!

1010
01:01:28,419 --> 01:01:29,461
Okay.

1011
01:01:29,461 --> 01:01:30,479
I'll see you later.

1012
01:01:30,479 --> 01:01:32,353
- Okay.
- Let's go.

1013
01:01:32,353 --> 01:01:34,666
Let's take it over there.

1014
01:01:36,474 --> 01:01:39,554
Let's see who's the prettiest.

1015
01:01:39,554 --> 01:01:42,413
One, two, three. Make a heart.

1016
01:01:42,413 --> 01:01:44,264
Make a big heart.

1017
01:01:44,264 --> 01:01:46,527
Good girl.

1018
01:01:48,699 --> 01:01:51,259
Hello, teachers.

1019
01:01:56,614 --> 01:01:58,334
[Jungwoon Elementary School Sports Day]

1020
01:02:15,712 --> 01:02:18,257
One, two, three.

1021
01:02:18,257 --> 01:02:20,590
Peekaboo!

1022
01:02:22,732 --> 01:02:25,667
All right, moms and dads, please come in.

1023
01:02:25,667 --> 01:02:28,767
Kids, hurry up and get ready.

1024
01:02:30,330 --> 01:02:33,210
Woo Joo, let's go inside.

1025
01:02:34,735 --> 01:02:38,367
[Saetbyeol Daycare Annual Recital]

1026
01:02:41,591 --> 01:02:44,052
Woo Joo.

1027
01:02:44,052 --> 01:02:45,196
Woo Joo.

1028
01:02:46,257 --> 01:02:47,303
Woo Joo?

1029
01:02:47,303 --> 01:02:48,207
Where are you going?

1030
01:02:48,207 --> 01:02:51,256
I'll go get him.

1031
01:02:51,256 --> 01:02:53,443
Woo Joo!

1032
01:04:00,750 --> 01:04:03,323
Woo Joo!

1033
01:04:03,323 --> 01:04:05,533
You did so great today.

1034
01:04:05,533 --> 01:04:08,403
Between us, you can just accept this.

1035
01:04:08,403 --> 01:04:11,293
So, have you made up your mind?

1036
01:04:11,293 --> 01:04:13,024
I'm not living with him anymore.

1037
01:04:13,024 --> 01:04:15,571
Woo Joo, want to go on a date with me?

1038
01:04:15,571 --> 01:04:18,837
I should really get going now. Take care.

1039
01:04:18,837 --> 01:04:20,117
My heart feels heavy.

1040
01:04:20,117 --> 01:04:22,379
Watching those two is so frustrating.

1041
01:04:22,379 --> 01:04:25,029
If you still have feelings,
why are you leaving?

1042
01:04:25,029 --> 01:04:26,449
I'm taking the evening flight.

1043
01:04:26,449 --> 01:04:29,315
I'm moving there for good.
